Job Title: Recycling Plant Operations manager

Peachtree Networks is a growing international telecom company with multiple international offices that offers talented and driven individuals the opportunity to grow their career in an exciting and professional field.

At Peachtree Networks we cover 100% of your Medical Insurance fees (after probation period)

Responsibilities:
Identify bottlenecks. Adjusting and reallocate resources strategically
Define, propose and implement the annual plan
Identify and set the target for projects’ timeframes
Manage and evaluate procedures to ensure productivity, efficiency, accuracy and minimize downtime
Develop and implement policies and procedures for catastrophic loss (CAT) situations
Analyze budgets and continuously monitor and control production costs and identify/rectify waste measures
Implement cost control procedures
Manage all teams within the production department in conjunction with the HR department
Coordinate after-hours emergency crews and work as required

The ideal candidate will possess:
Post-secondary courses in business/project/construction management
5 years Construction/Restoration/Insurance experience preferred
3 years’ experience in a leadership role
Experience in recycling plants
Experience and knowledge of provincial health & safety standards
Knowledge of project management
Willing to work evenings, on-call and weekends when requested
COPASST support, investigation of work accidents, indicators and safety inspections

Peachtree Networks is a growing international telecom company with multiple international offices that offers talented and driven individuals the opportunity to grow their career in an exciting and professional field.

At Peachtree Networks we cover 100% of your Medical Insurance fees (after probation period)

Responsibilities:
Identify bottlenecks. Adjusting and reallocate resources strategically
Define, propose and implement the annual plan
Identify and set the target for projects’ timeframes
Manage and evaluate procedures to ensure productivity, efficiency, accuracy and minimize downtime
Develop and implement policies and procedures for catastrophic loss (CAT) situations
Analyze budgets and continuously monitor and control production costs and identify/rectify waste measures
Implement cost control procedures
Manage all teams within the production department in conjunction with the HR department
Coordinate after-hours emergency crews and work as required
Identify performance measurements and propose actions needed to improve performance
Follow all safety policies and procedures to support a safe working environment, including safe operation of machines and equipment
Implement and enforce quality control and tracking programs to meet quality objectives
Utilize equipment in the most productive way, arrange maintenance on equipment, assist on the equipment procurement process

The ideal candidate will possess:
Post-secondary courses in business/project/construction management
5 years Construction/Restoration/Insurance experience preferred
3 years’ experience in a leadership role
Experience in recycling plants
Experience and knowledge of provincial health & safety standards
Knowledge of project management
Willing to work evenings, on-call and weekends when requested
COPASST support, investigation of work accidents, indicators and safety inspections
